response_dict.word_problem:
Samantha bought a packet of flour that weighs $3.84$ kilograms. She wants to divide the flour equally into $4$ smaller bags for baking.
\begin{enumerate}
  \item How much flour, in kilograms, will be in each bag? Give your answer correct to $2$ decimal places.
  \item Round the amount of flour in each bag to the nearest whole number, $1$ decimal place and $2$ decimal places.
\end{enumerate}

response_dict.solution:
Step 1: Divide $3.84$ kilograms by $4$.

\[
\frac{3.84}{4} = 0.96
\]

So, each bag will have $0.96$ kilograms of flour.

Step 2: Round $0.96$ to the required number of decimal places.

\begin{itemize}
  \item To the nearest whole number: $0.96$ rounds to $1$
  \item To $1$ decimal place: $0.96$ rounds to $1.0$
  \item To $2$ decimal places: $0.96$ (already $2$ decimal places)
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Answer:}

\begin{enumerate}
  \item Each bag will have $0.96$ kilograms of flour.
  \item Rounded to the nearest whole number: $1$ kilogram; to $1$ decimal place: $1.0$ kilograms; to $2$ decimal places: $0.96$ kilograms.
\end{enumerate}

